The paper discusses adversarial training of deep neural networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a new method for adversarial learning with unlabeled data, which is a subfield of unsupervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper deals with adversarial attacks and defenses, it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
